name: Warung Mie Bakso Lidi
address: Jl. Gunung Merapi No.31A, Pemecutan, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80111, Indonesia
review 1: Came here around 8.30 and was very pleased with everything! Food arrived fast, service is great, and food is also delicious. I tried the bakmie ayam jamur and their sambal is amazing.
review 2:
Forgot to take a picture for our meals.
Husband is picky about food so he plays safe by ordering Yamien Jamur with Pangsit Kuah. The taste is not bad for him. I ordered Nasi Bakmoy Setengah Telur and it was fine although i imagine the soup will be garlicy-gingery and savoury turns out it' s garlicy which is fine. The problem is with Hakau, since my husband also has allergies with not-fresh-sea-food so he felt a bit itchy on his tongue. Overall it is a good place to have something warm while strolling Denpasar city.
review 3:
One the best noodle in the heart of Denpasar, this one is originally from Bandung, West Java. I ordered Bakmi (Manis/Seeet) Rica Komplit, very tasty and the chilli level just right for me. It came with meatballs (you can choose from chicken, beef or fish) as well as meat filled tofu and wontons. The portion of the noodle is generous, definitely full after eating it.

My wife ordered Yamien (Manis/Sweet)Ayam Kecap, suit those who likes sweet type of noodles. If you prefer salty type you can choose (Asin/Salty), it will goes well with the Ayam kecap too!

We also ordered Tahu Kok, Bakso Goreng, Otak Otak Goreng . All of them were taste good. Bakso goreng is crispy inside out and it is served with sweet chilli sauce.

The place is inside a shophouse and they have tables outside too. Even though located on the road side, I found the place is very clean, the cutlery is covered so it wont get dusty. Parking is available on the road side, maybe it is easier to get a park during dinner because most the of the business in the area is closed after 5PM.

Will definitely comeback to try other menu.
review 4: The bakso goreng is tough , we can‚Äôt even chew it. Noodles is average taste.
review 5:
Moved to Bali since 2017 and i never found any good bakso or bakmie stall that match my expectations.

Then here we are mie bakso Lidi, i came from west java and i finally found this place who sell a really authentic and tasty yet affordable mie yamin in town!
I also already tried a bunch of another stall for bakmie ayam, and the taste just so so.

I will come back here on and on! Juara!

The place is pretty clean

Either eat here or take away.

name: Greenshot Vegan Vegetarian Coffee
address: Jl. Gn. Agung No.99C, Pemecutan, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80119, Indonesia
review 1: Ridiculously affordable vegan place! We stopped by yesterday for lunch and prices were hard to believe (I'm talking just Rp. 5,000 for the small Nasi Bakar and only about Rp. 1,000-Rp.2000 to add toppings). We tried just about all the mushroom items on their menu - delicious! Our favorites were the jumbo Nasi Bakar (priced at just Rp. 18,000 + we added tofu and tempe for an additional Rp. 2000), Crispy Mushrooms, and Vegan Sate (made out of mushrooms). Would definitely come back!
review 2:
Taste like simple homemade food that cook with love and care.

Very Affordable for fresh.
Love that I can‚Äôt taste the Msg in the food like some other vegetarian restaurant.

Def recomment especially if you‚Äôre tourist that wanna feel the authentic Indonesian food and ambiance.
review 3: I tried their nasi bakar and rawon. Both taste so-so. Nasi bakar way below my expectation. It only tastes spicy from sambal, they didn't put spices and herbs for the rice. Overall it really needs more seasoning. Their rawon also out of place. It didn't taste like rawon at all, it tastes mushroom broth. I can tell at my first bite, they don't use onion nor garlic and substitute it with mushroom broth. Well, I guess they're allium free vegan restaurant.
review 4:
Fantastic vegan nasi bakar, my favourite is with additional bunga papaya, jantung pisang & sambal bongkot.
The rawon jamur is delicious, and the crispy mushroom a nice snack to start with.
One of my favourite place to order from in Bali, all categories ‚ú¥Ô∏è

name: warung kasih vegan (vegetarian)
address: Jl. Setia Budi No.37, Pemecutan Kaja, Kec. Denpasar Utara, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80111, Indonesia

review 1: One of my favorite breakfast whenever I visited Bali. Ordered via goshop, as they are not available on gofood. The Best Nasi Campur Bali Vegan, run out fast. Order before 8 am, otherwise you might not get it.
review 2: The best vegan nasi campur in Bali. Cheap and delicious, authentic balinese taste
review 3: This is a small vegetarian warung but quite popular. It serves balinese vegetarian food like nasi campur bali and lawar. It opens in the morning so people could have breakfast but it closes quite quickly because their food runs out fast because of the large number of customers. When you pass by at the right time in the morning (around 7 a.m. to 9 a.m.) make sure to drop by and have breakfast here.
review 4: The other Vegan restaurants with balinese cuisines.
review 5: Cheap and large variety of food

review 1:
Spacious dining area and located in the heart of the city. The dishes were cooked fresh and I especially enjoyed the "Gondo" vegetable.

The staff were friendly and the place was passable for cleanliness.

I would recommend the Nasi Campur Spesial with all of the food choices available in one plate.

It's an okay place to bring a lot of friends. Smaller groups or couples are more recommended because of the seating availability.
